  "details": "Libtar is a C library for manipulating POSIX tar files. It handles adding and extracting files to/from a tar archive. Requires gcc, make, and zlib.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nAfter tar_close(), libtar.c releases the memory pointed to by pointer t. After tar_close() is called in the list() function, it continues to use pointer t: free_longlink_longname(t-&gt;th_buf) . As a result, the released memory is used (use-after-free).(CVE-2021-33640)",
